channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Confessions of a 1980s flight attendant
item.description: Ann Hood, a best-selling author, has recounted her adventures working as cabin crew on TWA flights in the 1980s in a book detailing the highs and lows of life during the early jet age.

item.title: US cricket team advances to second round in Twenty20 World Cup debut
item.description: The United States cricket team has made more history by qualifying for the second round in its Twenty20 World Cup debut after its last group game against Ireland was washed out in Florida

item.title: Congress’ defense fight to focus on pay raises, total military spending
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: You may owe the IRS on Monday — skipping it could cost you hundreds
item.description: Millions of Americans could owe money to the IRS on June 17, with fines for missing payment on the rise.

item.title: June 13, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The US-backed Gaza ceasefire proposal doesn't meet Hamas' demands for an end to the war, a senior official has told CNN. Osama Hamdan also said that "no one has an idea" how many of the hostages held in the enclave are alive.

item.title: Mexican shelters see crowding south of the border as Biden's asylum ban takes hold
item.description: Some shelters south of the U.S. border are caring for many more migrants now that the Biden administration stopped considering most asylum requests

item.title: Pic captures beachgoer minutes before she was run over by Horry police truck. Woman named
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: Infectious bird flu survived milk pasteurization in lab test. Here's what to know.
item.description: An experiment found "small but detectable" amounts of infectious H5N1 virus in milk after it was pasteurized for 15 seconds.

item.title: Biden and Zelensky lay out new US support for Ukraine
item.description: US President Joe Biden and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signed a new security agreement Thursday as world leaders gathered for the G7 summit in Italy.

item.title: Beachgoer fatally struck by police truck on South Carolina beach, highway patrol says
item.description: Authorities say a woman died after being struck by a police truck on a South Carolina beach

item.title: NASA's Voyager 1, the most distant spacecraft from Earth, is doing science again after problem
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: Justice Department won't prosecute Garland after House contempt vote
item.description: The House voted Wednesday to hold Attorney General Merrick Garland in contempt of Congress.

item.title: Supreme Court maintains access to abortion pill in unanimous decision
item.description: The Supreme Court has issued a decision on whether the US Food and Drug Administration overstepped its authority by expanding access to the abortion pill mifepristone.

item.title: Titan submersible implosion investigation taking longer than planned: Coast Guard
item.description: The investigation into the ill-fated Titan submersible's dive to the location of the Titanic will now take longer than expected, according to the U.S. Coast Guard.

item.title: “Walks like a duck, swims like a duck”: Sonia Sotomayor torches Supreme Court’s bump stock ruling
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: Biden meets with Pope Francis at G7 summit
item.description: President Biden and Pope Francis met in Italy Friday during the G7 summit where world leaders discussed the influence and potential perils of artificial intelligence with the pontiff. CBS News chief White House correspondent Nancy Cordes reports.

item.title: Trump in Washington for meetings with Republican allies
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is back in Washington for the first time since becoming the presumptive Republican nominee as well as a convicted felon. Follow here for the latest live news updates.

item.title: Putin pledges a cease-fire in Ukraine if Kyiv withdraws from occupied regions
item.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin proposed an immediate cease-fire in Ukraine and to begin negotiations if Kyiv started withdrawing troops from the four regions annexed by Moscow in 2022 and renounced plans to join NATO

item.title: 2 men die after falling into manure tanker at New York farm
item.description: One of the men tried to retrieve a piece of equipment that had fallen into the manure tanker, New York police said.
